<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - FULLER 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - ASSEMBLE - SHIFT LEVER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>SHIFT LEVER</title>
        <figure id="f13032a4" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G13032a4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 104. Shift Lever Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f13032a4">Figure 104.</hotlnk>
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure the housing in a vise with the bottom facing upward.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a high temperature grease to the O-ring and insert it in the housing tower inside
                groove.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the spade pin and insert it in the housing tower spade pin bore.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a high temperature grease to the shift lever pivot ball.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the spade pin groove on the shift lever pivot ball with the spade pin, and install the
                gear shift lever in the housing tower.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With dished-side up toward the spring, install the washer over the shift lever.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a tension spring driver to install the tension spring under the housing lugs. Seat the
                tension spring one coil at a time (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13032a5">Figure 105</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the assembly from the vise.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the rubber boot over the gear shift lever and against the housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13032a5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G13032a5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 105. Seating Tension Spring</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
